item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: rossk3lly
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: About me
item.dc:creator: rossk3lly
item.content:encoded: My name is Ross Kelly. I am a Creative Digital Media student currently studying in the Institute of Technology Blanchardstown. I have learned many professional skills and personal skills, for example learning to use different softwares and improving my creative thinking and presentation skills. I am a motivated and personable individual. I work well as part of a team or by myself.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: rossk3lly
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Photography
item.dc:creator: rossk3lly
item.content:encoded:
I enjoy all aspects from Portraits and Wildlife to Landscape and Cars. I own a Nikon D3100 and mainly use my 35mm 1.8 lens. When I edit my photos I use Photoshop CC or Lightroom. Photography is a passion of mine and i hope to get better at it. During my second year in college I studied a photography module. During the module I learned many skills and techniques. For example, I was shown how to use both Canon and Nikon Dslrs, how to set up photography lights, and how to take product shots. This was probably one of my favourite modules as I had prior experience with Nikon Dsrls and it gave me the opportunity to develop my skills. Here are some examples of my photography work. I have chosen these images to give you a broad overview of my style of photography. Hover over the image for a short description.

  No Country for Old Men ReDub This is an Audio re-dub I did for my Sound Design module in college. In this clip I made all the audio from scratch except the background ambience sound. The dialogue was voiced over by my father and I. I used Premier pro to edit the sound and audio Drive movie scene - Complete Audio ReDub This is another example of audio re-dubbing. I was given the footage with no sound at all and the task was to to try replicate the original scene from the film "Drive". Overall i am happy with how it came out. ITB Election 2016 Vox Pop This is a VoxPop that myself and 3 friends made around the ITB college campus. The aim for the video was to see who the students were voting for and why. We used a Canon Dslr, TriPod and Boom kit to capture the footage. It was a good experience and I would like to do it again on another topic. After capturing the footage we individually edited the clips together. Oblivious  This is a short film I made for my second year group project. I made it with three college friends. My main role in this project was to film and edit. The idea behind thefilm was to raise awareness about the homeless situation in Ireland. To film we used a Nikon and Canon Dslr and it was edited on Premier Pro. Overall we we're happy with the outcome and received good feedback from the judging panel. Music Video Edit This is a music video that I edited. The aim was to sync the audio with the footage and to give it a natural flow. I edited it in Premier Pro and experimented with a range of different editing techniques. The use of transitions and warp stabilisers are examples. The Recession in Ireland I made during as part of an assignment in second year with a classmate. It was my first time making a documentary type film. The documentary breaks down what the recession was, how it affected Ireland, two interviews involving people who were affected and if Ireland has recovered. The equipment that was used included my Nikon Dsrl, a video tripod and sound kit with a boom.The sound and footage was edited on Premier Pro. Plasti Clasy Promo Here is an example of an product advertisement I made. It was for a company called Plasti Clay. To advertise it I decided to make a creative video that shows the viewer what they can do with the clay and in my video it shows them how to make a footballer. For the second half of the video i experimented with stop motion to replicate a live football match. I enjoyed making this project.
